-- в”Ђв”Ђ Rippling в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Rippling is an all-in-one workforce management platform unifying HR, payroll, IT device management, and finance tools on a single employee record for global companies.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Modular per-employee-per-month pricing plus a monthly base platform fee; custom quotes$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$From $8 per employee per month (plus a base platform fee), with total cost varying by modules$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2016, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$4,000+ employees (as of 2025)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English, with support for multi-country payroll and localization in dozens of countries$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Rippling Review 2026: Pricing, Features, HR, IT and Payroll Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Rippling unifies HR, payroll, IT, and finance in one platform. See 2026 pricing, features, pros and cons, and how the modular pricing model works.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Rippling is a workforce management platform that unifies HR, payroll, benefits administration, IT device and app management, and finance tools around a single source-of-truth employee record, so that when an employee is hired, promoted, or terminated, changes automatically propagate across every connected system. The company was founded in April 2016 by Parker Conrad and Prasanna Sankar, with Conrad also known as a co-founder of Zenefits; Rippling is headquartered in San Francisco, California, with additional offices including New York, Chicago, and Pune, India. As of 2025, Rippling reported serving more than 20,000 customers worldwide and employing more than 4,000 people across offices on four continents, and the company has been privately valued at roughly $16.8 billion as of a May 2025 funding round. Rippling's product suite spans core HR (employee records, onboarding, org charts), US and international payroll, benefits administration, time and attendance, PEO services, IT management (automated laptop provisioning, app and SaaS management, mobile device management), and finance tools such as corporate cards, expense management, and bill pay, all built on Rippling's own compliance and employment infrastructure across many countries. Pricing is modular and not fully self-serve: the base Rippling Unity platform starts around $8 per employee per month plus a mandatory monthly base fee (commonly cited around $35), and each additional module a company activates, such as payroll, benefits, or IT device management, carries its own separate per-employee-per-month charge, meaning effective total costs commonly range from roughly $20 to $35+ per employee per month depending on which modules are selected; exact enterprise pricing requires a custom quote from Rippling's sales team, and third-party contract-data aggregators have reported median annual Rippling contract values in the range of roughly $39,700 to $40,100 based on real purchase records. Rippling competes most directly with Gusto, Justworks, Deel, and BambooHR, but differentiates itself by combining HR, IT, and finance in one unified system rather than offering HR alone, which appeals particularly to fast-growing, distributed, or global companies that want to reduce the number of disconnected point solutions and manual data syncing between systems.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '7f58ae22-1c44-4f9a-9b61-75861272aaaa';

