-- в”Ђв”Ђ Rive в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Rive is a real-time interactive design and animation tool that lets designers and developers create animated, state-driven graphics for apps, games, and websites.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium with per-seat monthly subscription tiers plus a custom enterprise plan$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free plan available; paid plans start at $9/seat/month (Cadet)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2016, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$~75 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Rive Review 2026: Pricing, Features, and Interactive Animation Tool Guide$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Rive is a real-time interactive animation and design tool for apps, games, and web. See 2026 pricing plans, features, pros and cons, and use cases.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Rive is a real-time interactive design and animation tool that lets designers and developers create vector-based animations with built-in interactivity, state machines, and lightweight runtimes that render natively on web, iOS, Android, game engines, and other platforms without needing to export video files. The company behind Rive was founded in 2016 in San Francisco, California, originally under the name 2Dimensions, and built early tools including Nima and Flare before consolidating its product and company brand into Rive in December 2019 under co-founders and identical twin brothers Guido Rosso (CEO) and Luigi Rosso (CTO). Rive has raised approximately $14 million in funding from investors including Andreessen Horowitz, Two Sigma Ventures, Unusual Ventures, and BMW i Ventures, and employed roughly 75 people as of 2026. The core differentiator of Rive versus traditional animation tools like After Effects or Lottie is its State Machine feature, which lets designers define interactive states and transitions (such as a button's hover, press, and loading states) directly inside the design tool, then ship that interactivity to production via small, fast runtimes rather than requiring a developer to hand-code the logic separately; this makes Rive popular for animated app icons, onboarding flows, game characters, and interactive UI elements where file size and real-time responsiveness matter, and notable users include companies like Duolingo. Rive's pricing is freemium and per-seat: the Free plan supports 3 collaborative files with limited AI agent access; the Cadet plan is $9 per seat per month (up to 3 seats) and unlocks unlimited files and .riv file export; the Voyager plan is $32 per seat per month (up to 25 seats) and adds shared libraries, embeddable URL hosting, and more advanced AI agent credits; and the Enterprise plan is $120 per seat per month, intended for organizations with $10 million or more in annual revenue, and includes subteam workspaces, custom S3 storage, SSO, SOC 2 Type II compliance, dedicated support, and centralized billing. Rive's collaborative editor supports real-time multiplayer editing similar to Figma, and its open runtime libraries are widely used by mobile and game developers who need lightweight, interactive vector graphics rather than static image or video assets.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'dcc42744-8093-4da4-b78b-0290e5d5def0';

