-- в”Ђв”Ђ Roadmunk в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Roadmunk is a product roadmapping tool that helps product teams visualize, prioritize, and communicate strategy across timeline, swimlane, and Kanban roadmap views, now part of Tempo's Strategic Roadmaps suite.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Tiered per-user subscription billed annually, plus a custom Enterprise plan$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$19/user/month (Starter plan)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Part of Tempo (parent company); Roadmunk team historically small (11-50 employees pre-acquisition)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Toronto, Canada (originally); now operates under Tempo, headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Roadmunk Review 2026: Pricing, Features, and Product Roadmap Software Guide$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Roadmunk is a product roadmapping tool, now part of Tempo's Strategic Roadmaps suite. See 2026 pricing plans, features, pros and cons, and use cases.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Roadmunk is a product roadmapping and prioritization tool that helps product managers and cross-functional teams build, visualize, and share roadmaps in multiple formats, including timeline views, swimlane views, and Kanban-style boards, along with prioritization frameworks for scoring and ranking features or initiatives. The company was founded in 2013 and originally headquartered in Toronto, Canada, before being acquired by Tempo, a project and portfolio management software company, in November 2021; since the acquisition, Roadmunk has been rebranded and continues to be sold as 'Strategic Roadmaps (Roadmunk)' within Tempo's broader portfolio of Jira-ecosystem and enterprise agile planning products, with Tempo itself headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts. Roadmunk's core use case is letting product teams collect feedback and requests, score and prioritize items using built-in frameworks, and generate polished, presentation-ready roadmap visuals to share with executives, sales teams, and customers, without needing design or spreadsheet work; it integrates with tools like Jira, Trello, and other product management systems to pull in existing backlog data. Pricing follows a tiered per-user model billed primarily on an annual basis: the Starter plan is priced around $19 per user per month for individuals or very small teams needing basic roadmapping; the Business plan is around $49 per user per month and adds collaboration features suited to small teams, such as feedback management and portfolio-level roadmap views; the Professional plan is around $99 per user per month with more advanced sharing and integration capabilities; and an Enterprise plan offers custom pricing with additional features like single sign-on (SSO), priority support, and a dedicated customer success manager. All plans include a 14-day free trial. As a tool now embedded within Tempo's Strategic Roadmaps product line, Roadmunk is most relevant to product managers already using or adjacent to the Atlassian/Jira ecosystem, and it competes with dedicated roadmapping tools like ProductPlan, Aha!, and Productboard.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'f9bd53de-0b4e-4fb9-8496-c57e0f61e8eb';

